# Everything in this repo is built and run inside Linux containers, so every text
# file must keep LF endings regardless of the OS it was committed from. Without this,
# a commit made on Windows (core.autocrlf=true) can rewrite shell-interpreted files —
# the inline `bash -c` block in docker-compose.yml, for one — with CRLF, which injects
# stray \r characters and breaks them at runtime with confusing errors.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Lockfiles are generated artifacts: normalise them but never let a diff tool try to
# merge them line-by-line.
package-lock.json -diff
